-- Hong Kong stocks jump, led by property developers
-- 
-- Mon May 12, 2014 01:55AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, May 12 (Reuters) - Shares of Hong Kong property developers surged on Monday amid speculation the government may change the city's stamp duty rules, with the real estate sub-sector index <.HSNP> jumping more than 3.5 percent.

Cheung Kong Holdings <0001.HK>, controlled by billionaire Li Ka-shing, soared 4.5 percent, New World Development <0017.HK> gained 4.3 percent, Henderson Land <0012.HK> rose 3.5 percent, while Sun Hung Kai Properties Ltd <0016.HK> was up 3.4 percent.  The benchmark Hang Seng Index <.HSI> rose more than 2 percent on the back of gains in the property sector.